---
import Base from '../../layouts/Base.astro';
const reviewed = "July 2026";
---
<Base
  title="Company Formation in Mongolia 2026: LLC, JSC & Mining Investment | ARM Management"
  description="A guide to setting up a company in Mongolia — LLC and JSC structures, foreign ownership rules under the Investment Law, mining sector investment, and the incorporation process in 2026."
>
  <main>
    <section class="page-hero">
      <div class="page-hero__bg" style="background-image:url('/images/ed-dubai.jpg')"></div>
      <div class="page-hero__overlay"></div>
      <div class="page-hero__content container">
        <span class="eyebrow">Guide · Mongolia Company Formation</span>
        <h1>Setting Up a Company in Mongolia</h1>
        <p>Mongolia is one of the world's most resource-rich frontier economies — copper, coal, gold and rare earths underpin its growth. Here is how foreign investors incorporate and access the mining sector in 2026.</p>
        <div class="btn-row" style="justify-content:flex-start;margin-top:30px">
          <a href="/contact" class="btn-primary">Speak With a Senior Advisor →</a>
          <a href="/services/company-formation" class="btn-secondary">Company Formation Services</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
    <section class="section section--warm">
      <div class="container--narrow">
        <div class="guide-meta reveal">
          <span><strong>Last reviewed:</strong> {reviewed}</span>
          <span><strong>Primary sources:</strong>
            <a href="https://www.investmongolia.gov.mn" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Invest Mongolia Agency</a>,
            <a href="https://burtgel.gov.mn" target="_blank" rel="noopener">General Registration Authority (GRA)</a>
          </span>
        </div>
        <div class="prose">
          <p class="reveal lede">Mongolia is a landlocked economy between China and Russia with one of the world's highest concentrations of untapped mineral wealth — the Oyu Tolgoi copper-gold mine (Tier 1 global asset) and Tavan Tolgoi coal deposit anchor the economy. The Investment Law 2013 (as amended) guarantees investment stability, limits nationalisation and provides a legal framework for foreign investment across sectors.</p>
          <h2 class="reveal">Key facts for 2026</h2>
          <div class="rate-table reveal">
            <table>
              <thead><tr><th>Parameter</th><th>Detail</th></tr></thead>
              <tbody>
                <tr><td>Corporate income tax</td><td>10% (standard rate, one of Asia's lowest)</td></tr>
                <tr><td>VAT</td><td>10% (standard rate)</td></tr>
                <tr><td>Foreign ownership</td><td>100% for most sectors (strategic sectors require government approval)</td></tr>
                <tr><td>Mining royalty</td><td>2.5–5% of sales value depending on mineral type</td></tr>
                <tr><td>Investment stability agreement</td><td>Available for investments over MNT 10 billion (≈ USD 3 million)</td></tr>
              </tbody>
            </table>
          </div>
          <h2 class="reveal">Corporate structures and strategic sector rules</h2>
          <p class="reveal">The standard vehicle is a <strong>Limited Liability Company (LLC / ХХК)</strong> registered with the General Registration Authority. A <strong>Joint Stock Company (JSC / ХК)</strong> is used for larger enterprises or listed entities. Foreign investors can own 100% in most sectors. However, the Law on Prohibition of Mineral Resources and Strategic Assets imposes a strategic-sector screening for investments in mining, energy, telecommunications, finance and media where a single foreign investor would acquire 33%+ or multiple foreign investors would acquire 49%+ of a strategic company — requiring Parliamentary approval. This is a significant constraint for large mining M&amp;A transactions.</p>
          <h2 class="reveal">Mining investment framework</h2>
          <p class="reveal">Mining licences are issued by the Mineral Resources Authority of Mongolia (MRAM). Exploration licences are freely transferable; mining licences are non-transferable without MRAM approval. Mongolia levies a <strong>windfall tax</strong> on copper and gold when prices exceed defined thresholds. Foreign-owned mining companies pay the standard 10% CIT plus a 5% surtax, bringing effective mining CIT to approximately 25% including royalties. Investment Stability Agreements (ISAs) can lock in tax rates and government commitments for up to 30 years for qualifying projects.</p>
          <h2 class="reveal">The incorporation process</h2>
          <ul class="reveal">
            <li>Register an LLC with the General Registration Authority (GRA) — online or in-person; 1–3 business days.</li>
            <li>Register with the General Department of Taxation for CIT and VAT.</li>
            <li>For mining: obtain exploration or mining licences from MRAM.</li>
            <li>For strategic-sector M&amp;A: notify and obtain approval from the Government Implementing Agency (Cabinet Secretariat).</li>
            <li>Open a corporate bank account at a Mongolian commercial bank.</li>
          </ul>
          <h2 class="reveal">Frequently asked questions</h2>
          <div class="reveal">
            <div class="faq-item"><h4>Can a foreigner own 100% of a Mongolian company?</h4><p>Yes, for most sectors. Strategic sectors (mining, energy, telecoms, finance, media) require government or Parliamentary approval for foreign acquisitions above defined thresholds.</p></div>
            <div class="faq-item"><h4>What is the corporate tax rate in Mongolia?</h4><p>10% standard rate — one of Asia's lowest. Mining companies pay an additional 5% surtax. Royalties of 2.5–5% on mineral sales value apply on top of CIT.</p></div>
            <div class="faq-item"><h4>What is an Investment Stability Agreement?</h4><p>A bilateral contract between the investor and the Mongolian government that locks in agreed tax rates and regulatory terms for up to 30 years. Available for investments above MNT 10 billion (≈ USD 3 million).</p></div>
          </div>
          <h2 class="reveal">Official sources</h2>
          <ul class="sources reveal">
            <li><a href="https://www.investmongolia.gov.mn" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Invest Mongolia Agency</a></li>
            <li><a href="https://burtgel.gov.mn" target="_blank" rel="noopener">General Registration Authority (GRA)</a></li>
            <li><a href="https://mram.gov.mn" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Mineral Resources Authority of Mongolia (MRAM)</a></li>
          </ul>
          <p class="reveal disclaimer">This guide is general information prepared by ARM Management and is current as at {reviewed}. It is not legal advice. Confirm with Invest Mongolia or a qualified advisor before incorporating.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
    <section class="cta-section guide-cta">
      <span class="eyebrow is-center reveal" style="justify-content:center">Speak With ARM</span>
      <h2 class="reveal">Access Mongolia's resource economy through the right investment structure.</h2>
      <div class="btn-row reveal">
        <a href="/contact" class="btn-primary">Schedule a Consultation →</a>
        <a href="/services/company-formation" class="btn-secondary">Company Formation Services</a>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>
